for instance,

00:59:42.660 --> 00:59:44.950
of communism as a system.

00:59:44.950 --> 00:59:47.720
A political system
that -- how is it --

00:59:47.720 --> 00:59:52.140
the ends justified
the means, right?

00:59:52.140 --> 00:59:56.810
So, when I was studying
utopianism in Brazil I worked

00:59:56.810 --> 00:59:59.710
with a different notion
of utopia that I called

00:59:59.710 --> 01:00:03.380
in another book I
co-edited a few years ago,

01:00:03.380 --> 01:00:05.200
existential utopia.

01:00:05.200 --> 01:00:07.540
And, so, by existential
utopia, I mean,

01:00:07.540 --> 01:00:12.990
utopia not as a goal
that's somehow hovers above

01:00:12.990 --> 01:00:17.050
and beyond society in the
future, but as the utopia

01:00:17.050 --> 01:00:21.240
as something that is imbedded
in every day practices, right?

01:00:21.240 --> 01:00:25.590
And that's why, for instance,
I think utopia is related

01:00:25.590 --> 01:00:27.310
to the environment
are so powerful,

01:00:27.310 --> 01:00:29.630
because the environment
is something you encounter

01:00:29.630 --> 01:00:31.170
on an everyday basis.

01:00:31.170 --> 01:00:32.970
It's not something out there.

01:00:32.970 --> 01:00:34.750
And, again, issues of leisure.

01:00:34.750 --> 01:00:41.620
People work every day, they
experience labor every day,

01:00:41.620 --> 01:00:45.240
so utopias of leisure
are not something

01:00:45.240 --> 01:00:48.220
that somehow could
exist in somewhere

01:00:48.220 --> 01:00:51.480
in a very distance future, but
they are something that speaks

01:00:51.480 --> 01:00:53.560
to our realities in the present.

01:00:53.560 --> 01:00:57.610
And I think that's the only way
that a concept, such as the one

01:00:57.610 --> 01:01:01.470
of utopia, can still be relevant
today, is if we think about it

01:01:01.470 --> 01:01:06.340
as operative on an everyday
basis and not as something

01:01:06.340 --> 01:01:10.540
that we should really try to
reach sometime in the future

01:01:10.540 --> 01:01:14.580
and that ends up being almost
oppressive in the present.

01:01:14.580 --> 01:01:18.640
So, to the country I think
utopias should make us feel

01:01:18.640 --> 01:01:22.180
uncomfortable in the
present, but in a good way.

01:01:22.180 --> 01:01:26.620
Showing us that the present can
be better, but not as some sort

01:01:26.620 --> 01:01:30.330
of an ideal that we always have
to match and we can never match.

01:01:30.330 --> 01:01:35.230
But as the kind of
making us slightly --

01:01:35.230 --> 01:01:37.540
how I should put this --

01:01:37.540 --> 01:01:40.080
slightly uncomfortable
where we sit knowing

01:01:40.080 --> 01:01:42.720
that we could be a
bit better, right?

01:01:42.720 --> 01:01:45.260
So, I think that's
the kind of utopia

01:01:45.260 --> 01:01:49.520
that is valuable
politically today, right,

01:01:49.520 --> 01:01:53.920
a utopia that makes us see
that things could be better,

01:01:53.920 --> 01:01:57.740
but that doesn't dictate how
they necessarily need to go

01:01:57.740 --> 01:02:04.980
and how you necessarily need
for them to be better, right?

